# keys.env.example
# =================
# Copy this file to `keys.env` (same folder) and fill in your key to enable the
# OPTIONAL "Ask (LLM)" tab in the dashboard. Everything else in the platform
# works WITHOUT this — the default router is rule-based and needs no key.
#
#   cp keys.env.example keys.env
#   # then edit keys.env and paste your real key below
#
# `keys.env` is gitignored, so your real key is never committed.

# Required to enable LLM routing:
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# When a key is present, the platform ALSO uses the LLM to explain failures
# (e.g. "model not trained" / "data not downloaded") in plain language. With no
# key, those failures still return a clear built-in message and fix steps — the
# key only adds a friendlier, LLM-written explanation on top.

# Optional: pin the model used for routing (otherwise a sensible default is used).
# WAFER_LLM_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
